e... but instead we get draught, draught again, and another draught =( not that they suck or anything just that they all do very little dmg compare to the mobs we fight at these lvl..<br>
<br>
I know draughts are fast casting and mana efficient, but everytime when I cast them on lvl 50+ mobs and see little or no hp decrease it's just depressing, yet at lvl 55 rogues get double backstab that allows them to do even greater dmg...<br>
<br>
I know when I finally hit 60 and get some decent AA points my wizard will rock again, such as 3500 crits!!!  it's the long wait that we have to go through that really annoys me <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pyrefly>Pyrefly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/8/03 12:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why does wizard suck so bad from lvl 50 to lvl 59?</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry to see that you think we suck 51-60.  Since level 49, I feel more powerful with every level.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I know draughts are fast casting and mana efficient, but everytime when I cast them on lvl 50+ mobs and see little or no hp decrease it's just depressing, yet at lvl 55 rogues get double backstab that allows them to do even greater dmg...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If you wanna see those HP move, try casting a rain and then chaining draughts while the rain is falling.  Grouping at 51 at the Underbulks in PoD by the castle (all red to me), the first 40% of the fight was taking on average, about 1-2 mins.  When I started nuking at 60%, it would be over in about 30sec.  Just make sure you're using your spells to their full potential.  Not to mention quadding....<br>
<br>
Yeah I really don't think that we suck 51-60.<br>
<br>
